Use Node.js + Express with TypeScript.

The backend must be configured and written in TypeScript.
Do not use plain JavaScript for backend source files unless it is required for configuration files.

Do not introduce another backend framework.

Separate code into:

routes
controllers
services
db
middleware
config
types

Use environment variables for configuration.

Use PostgreSQL through a centralized database service/module.

Use dotenv, cors, express.json and centralized error middleware.

Use multer or similar middleware when handling file uploads.

Do not implement a full local report lifecycle.

Do not create local report status workflow such as:

nove
prijate
v_rieseni
opravene
zamietnute

Do not implement technician assignment, operator roles, report history, or repair management.

Allowed backend responsibilities:

reverse geocode coordinates via Nominatim only in batch script (`npm run geocode:points`) or when adding new light points — persist result in `light_points.address`; UI reads from DB
provide street light data to frontend
manage street lights in admin area
support import/export of light points
validate report form data before forwarding
prepare multipart/form-data request for AUSEMIO/DPMK
keep technical integration logs without citizen personal data
keep configuration and mapping in one central place

Do not store citizen phone, email, report text, photos, or identity permanently.

Use clear service functions and avoid putting business logic directly in route files.

Use TypeScript types/interfaces for:

request payloads
service input/output data
database models
external integration payloads
configuration objects

Backend source files should use the .ts extension.
Build output, if needed, should be generated into a separate dist folder.